‘Converted to interpolated string’ works with the following code.

```cs
Console.WriteLine(String.Format("Hello World!{0}", 1.1));
// Converted to Console.WriteLine($"Hello World!{1.1}");
 ```

However, it does not work with `InvariantCulture`

```cs
Console.WriteLine(String.Format(CultureInfo.InvariantCulture, "Hello World!{0}", 1.1));
// Expect to convert to Console.WriteLine(FormattableString.Invariant($"Hello World!{1.1}"));
```

VariantCulture is often used in text processing where the same result must be obtained.

